notes: 12th men: CD McMillan (NZ) and IJ Harvey (Aus).
Martyn brought up 1000 runs in one day internationals when he reached 34, off his 43rd ball faced, during Styris' first over.
Australia: 50 from 81 balls, 46 minutes; 100 from 143 balls, 98 minutes; 150 from 214 balls, 144 minutes.
DR Martyn: 50 from 52 balls, 67 minutes, 8x4, 1x6; 100 from 118 balls, 115 minutes, 12x4, 1x6. 116* is his highest one day international score, and his first century.
GD McGrath: 11 is his highest one day international score.
Australia 4th wicket partnership (Martyn/ ME Waugh): 50 from 72 balls, 47 minutes.
Australia 10th wicket partnership (Martyn/McGrath): 31 runs from 45 balls, 29 minutes is the highest for Australia against New Zealand.
New Zealand: 50 from 52 balls, 38 minutes; 100 from 138 balls, 101 minutes; 150 from 204 balls, 147 minutes.
New Zealand 3rd wicket partnership (Nevin/Fleming): 50 from 48 minutes, 66 balls; 100 from 134 balls, 93 minutes.
ML Hayden debut bowling in one day internationals.
Play delayed for 17 minutes at 9:04 pm as several of the lighting towers failed after 40.3 overs.
New Zealand innings: 1x5 ball over (35th over - SK Warne's 8th over, called by umpire DB Cowie)
